cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper deals with image-based 2D pose estimation for pedestrian detection and tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The application of this technique is for predicting pedestrian intentions in naturalistic driving conditions, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses CNN-based methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of pedestrian safety, which is relevant to computer security (cs.CR).
